{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 8).",
    "The state vector is first processed by a fully connected NN with one layer.",
    "In order to process the vector to a 2D matrix, the vector is reshaped to a 3D matrix first (e.g., R 512 → R 4x4x32).",
    "The reshaping process keeps the number of elements constant.",
    "Only the position is changed."
  ]
}